div.p: $ - continuous running activity. e.g., $ read data means continuously reading data

p.span:
X Y means that object "X" is continuously doing activity "a" on object "Y".
E.g. if X is USBCamReader, a is 'updates frame', Y is VideoFrame, it means USBCamReader is continuously 'updating frame' in VideoFrame.
A rectangle object indicates a non-processing object, i.e., such an object does not perform any processing operations by its own.

div.p: Such an object indicates a 'singleton' object, i.e., there is only one such object throughout the program.
An oval object indicates a processing object, and there may be many instances of such objects throughout the program
